|CKBRonin-sama Kernel|000

|CK0Ronin-sama Kernel is the passive Street Samurai capstone unlocked at Guild
Level 16. It uses the brain-mounted Cortex OS and has no activation command,
SP cost, Edge cost, or Heat cost.|000

|CKBCortex ascension|000
|CK0Reaching the capstone reconfigures the installed Cortex OS to ghost grade.
The kernel remains active while a GL16 Street Samurai has that ghost-grade
Cortex installed and the contract is active. Dashboard identifies RONIN KERNEL
as the Cortex process state.|000

|CKBEngagement telemetry|000
|CK0When a new attacker enters the engagement, the kernel reads the hostile
telemetry and attempts to establish Edge if capacity is available. It can also
answer incoming swings with an automatic slashing counterattack. These are
passive responses; no command is required.|000

|CKBKeeping it effective|000
|CK0The counter protocol benefits from the operator's combat development and
the Cortex's firmware effectiveness. Continued Cortex Rank improves both the
counter protocol's response rate and the force of its return strike. Poor Cortex
integrity or fragmentation can make the response less dependable, so the
capstone does not remove the need for maintenance.|000

|CK0Cortex Rank continues after the kernel comes online. Use samxp for rank
progress, dashboard for throughput and Cortex condition, and samhelp
maintenance when the host OS reports a problem.|000
